content.text:
Now let me reason through the fixes:

**Fix 1 & Fix 2** both target the same thing: the `.pf-v5-c-dropdown` class on line 2. Both rules say this class was removed in the new version and there is no `pf-v6-c-dropdown` equivalent. The instruction is to remove the class reference or replace it with appropriate custom CSS.

Looking at the code structure:
```scss
.co-operator-details__actions {
  .pf-v5-c-dropdown {
    height: fit-content;
  }
}
```

This is a nested SCSS selector that applies `height: fit-content` to elements with class `pf-v5-c-dropdown` inside `.co-operator-details__actions`. Since the `pf-v5-c-dropdown` class no longer exists in the target version, and PatternFly v6 uses the `MenuToggle` component instead of the old `Dropdown`, this entire rule block is dead CSS — it targets a class that will never be present in rendered output.

The correct approach is to remove the entire `.co-operator-details__actions` block since its only content is the dead `.pf-v5-c-dropdown` rule. Leaving an empty `.co-operator-details__actions {}` block would be dead code.

Let me write the cleaned-up file:

